'''Véronique Robert''' (1962<ref>Alexis Delcambre, [http://www.lemonde.fr/disparitions/article/2017/06/25/mort-de-la-journaliste-veronique-robert_5150824_3382.html La journaliste Véronique Robert était « une vraie professionnelle de la guerre], LeMonde.fr, 25 June 2017.{{fr icon}}</ref>&nbsp;– 24 June 2017) was a Franco-Swiss journalist and war correspondent, who died in a Paris hospital on 24 June 2017, at age 54, after being wounded in an explosion in [[Mosul]], Iraq, five days earlier, on 19 June.<ref name="theguardian1">{{cite web|author=Kim Willsher and Reuters|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/jun/24/veronique-robert-journalist-dies-paris-wounded-mosul-explosion-iraq|title=Franco-Swiss journalist dies in Paris after being injured in Mosul blast|publisher=The Guardian|date=24 June 2017|access-date=25 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/06/journalist-veronique-robert-dies-mosul-blast-wounds-170624130021869.html|title=Journalist Veronique Robert dies of Mosul blast wounds|publisher=Al Jazeera|access-date=24 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Chloe Farand|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/french-journalist-swiss-veronique-robert-dies-injuries-mosul-mine-explosion-reporting-isis-iraq-a7806401.html|title=French journalist dies of injuries after reporting on Isis war in Iraq|publisher=The Independent|access-date=24 June 2017}}</ref>

Robert was wounded in the same mine explosion that killed Iraqi journalist [[Bakhtiyar Haddad]] and fellow French journalist [[Stephane Villeneuve]], and wounded Samuel Foley, who works for ''[[Le Figaro]]''.<ref name="theguardian1"/> Robert and Villeneuve were working for [[France Télévisions]] on a report for the French TV documentary show ''[[Envoyé spécial]]''.<ref name="theguardian1"/>

In 2007, one of her sons was raped in Dubai, prompting her to launch a campaign against the authorities.<ref>[http://abcnews.go.com/2020/story?id=3932740 'They Destroyed Me': French Teen's Rape Case Exposes Dubai's Dark Side] ABC News, 12 December 2007.</ref><ref>[http://edition.cnn.com/2007/WORLD/meast/12/12/dubai.rape/ Dubai court jails boy's HIV rapist] CNN, 12 December 2007.</ref><ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2007/10/31/world/africa/31iht-dubai.4.8133097.html Dubai and rape: French youth tells his story] New York Times, 31 October 2007.</ref>

